    "image_url": "https://crowpeakbrewing.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/2.png",
    "description": "Canyon Cream Ale falls into the blonde or golden ale category. Characteristics of this beer style are a straw color with a white head. The aroma is of sweet malt with a hint of honey and a slightly fruity finish. This is a light-bodied beer with very low hop bitterness and no hop aroma or flavor. This beer is very drinkable especially for the craft beer novice (We call it our “gateway beer”). Canyon Cream Ale is brewed with the finest quality Pilsen malt with Carapils malt added for body adjustment and local honey added for flavor adjustment. Hallertau and Saaz hops are added to balance the sweet maltiness of this ale. Original Gravity is 11.2°P and alcohol by volume value is 5.0%.",
